title: `raise ValueError(f"Shape of passed values is {passed}, indices imply {implied}") ValueError: Shape of passed values is ...` during maDLC evaluation?

labels.name: howtousedlc
labels.description: issue regarding the use of DeepLabCut

body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

Hello,

This issue has been occurring with both newly created projects, as well as projects with several training iterations. Essentially, the network is trained like normal, and afterwards, on the evaluation phase, the following error is given:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\gui\evaluate_network.py", line 270, in evaluate_network
    deeplabcut.evaluate_network(
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\pose_estimation_tensorflow\core\evaluate.py", line 562, in evaluate_network
    evaluate_multianimal_full(
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\deeplabcut\pose_estimation_tensorflow\core\evaluate_multianimal.py", line 421, in evaluate_multianimal_full
    df_dist = pd.DataFrame(dist, columns=df.index)
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\frame.py", line 672, in __init__
    mgr = ndarray_to_mgr(
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\internals\construction.py", line 322, in ndarray_to_mgr
    _check_values_indices_shape_match(values, index, columns)
  File "D:\Applications\Anaconda3\envs\DEEPLABCUT\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\internals\construction.py", line 391, in _check_values_indices_shape_match
    raise ValueError(f"Shape of passed values is {passed}, indices imply {implied}")
ValueError: Shape of passed values is (2700, 250), indices imply (2700, 75)
```

There is a difference between projects in the error, where the 'ValueError: Shape of passed values is (2700, 250), indices imply (2700, 75)' error shows different values, but the rest of the error is identical.



### Operating System

Windows 10

### DeepLabCut version

In [2]: deeplabcut.__version__
Out[2]: '2.2rc3'

### DeepLabCut mode

multi animal

### Device type

gpu (GTX 1080ti)

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Using the new DEEPLABCUT conda environment
2. Use either DLC GUI or use ipython, error is the same
3. Extract and label frames, train network (dlcrnet_ms5 if that matters), all works as anticipated.
4. Evaluate network
5. Error occurs.

### Relevant log output

_No response_

### Anything else?

This issue is similar, but occurs in Analyze videos, rather than Evaluate network.
https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/issues/422
